cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for improving semantic similarity judgments and dialogue state tracking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for improving vector space representations, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of linguistic constraints, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques for dialogue state tracking, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves neural network techniques for improving vector space representations, which can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
